verses.text: And the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* said unto Moses , Depart , \add and\add* go up hence, thou and the people which thou hast brought up out of the land of Egypt , unto the land which I sware unto Abraham , to Isaac , and to Jacob , saying , Unto thy seed will I give it:
And I will send an angel before thee; and I will drive out the Canaanite , the Amorite , and the Hittite , and the Perizzite , the Hivite , and the Jebusite :
Unto a land flowing with milk and honey : for I will not go up in the midst of thee; for thou \add art\add* a stiffnecked people : lest I consume thee in the way. \p
¶ And when the people heard these evil tidings , they mourned : and no man did put on him his ornaments.

For the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* had said unto Moses , Say unto the children of Israel , Ye \add are\add* a stiffnecked people : I will come up into the midst of thee in a moment , and consume thee: therefore now put off thy ornaments from thee, that I may know what to do unto thee.
And the children of Israel stripped themselves of their ornaments by the mount Horeb. \p

And Moses took the tabernacle , and pitched it without the camp , afar off from the camp , and called it the Tabernacle of the congregation. And it came to pass, \add that\add* every one which sought the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* went out unto the tabernacle of the congregation , which \add was\add* without the camp.

And it came to pass, when Moses went out unto the tabernacle , \add that\add* all the people rose up , and stood every man \add at\add* his tent door , and looked after Moses , until he was gone into the tabernacle.
And it came to pass, as Moses entered into the tabernacle , the cloudy pillar descended , and stood \add at\add* the door of the tabernacle , and \add the \+nd LORD\+nd*\add* talked with Moses.
And all the people saw the cloudy pillar stand \add at\add* the tabernacle door : and all the people rose up and worshipped , every man \add in\add* his tent door.

And the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* spake unto Moses face to face , as a man speaketh unto his friend. And he turned again into the camp : but his servant Joshua , the son of Nun , a young man , departed not out of the tabernacle. \p

¶ And Moses said unto the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*, See , thou sayest unto me, Bring up this people : and thou hast not let me know whom thou wilt send with me. Yet thou hast said , I know thee by name , and thou hast also found grace in my sight.

Now therefore, I pray thee, if I have found grace in thy sight , shew me now thy way , that I may know thee, that I may find grace in thy sight : and consider that this nation \add is\add* thy people.
And he said , My presence shall go \add with thee\add*, and I will give thee rest.
And he said unto him, If thy presence go not \add with me\add*, carry us not up hence.

For wherein shall it be known here that I and thy people have found grace in thy sight ? \add is it\add* not in that thou goest with us? so shall we be separated , I and thy people , from all the people that \add are\add* upon the face of the earth.
And the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* said unto Moses , I will do this thing also that thou hast spoken : for thou hast found grace in my sight , and I know thee by name.
And he said , I beseech thee , shew me thy glory.

And he said , I will make all my goodness pass before thee, and I will proclaim the name of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* before thee; and will be gracious to whom I will be gracious , and will shew mercy on whom I will shew mercy.
And he said , Thou canst not see my face : for there shall no man see me, and live.
And the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* said , Behold, \add there is\add* a place by me, and thou shalt stand upon a rock :
And it shall come to pass, while my glory passeth by , that I will put thee in a clift of the rock , and will cover thee with my hand while I pass by :
And I will take away mine hand , and thou shalt see my back parts : but my face shall not be seen.
